:"2552"},{"range":"2690","text":"2650"},{"range":"2691","text":"2552"},"Replace `))⏎········` with `··)`",{"range":"2692","text":"2693"},{"range":"2694","text":"2343"},"Insert `⏎···`",{"range":"2695","text":"2696"},"Replace `·className=\"inline-flex·items-center·gap-1·ml-2·text-xs\"·title={`Due:·${reminder.date}${reminder.time·?·'·'·+·reminder.time·:·''}`}` with `⏎············className=\"inline-flex·items-center·gap-1·ml-2·text-xs\"⏎············title={`Due:·${reminder.date}${reminder.time·?·'·'·+·reminder.time·:·''}`}⏎··········`",{"range":"2697","text":"2698"},"Replace `filePath:·string,·content:·string` with `⏎··filePath:·string,⏎··content:·string⏎`",{"range":"2699","text":"2700"},"Replace `filePath:·string,·articleEl:·HTMLElement·|·null` with `⏎··filePath:·string,⏎··articleEl:·HTMLElement·|·null⏎`",{"range":"2701","text":"2702"},"Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/Users/macbook/github code/Nabu/src/renderer/src/features/pdf/PdfViewer.tsx:101:7\n   99 |     if (totalPages > 0 && initialPage && initialPage !== currentPage) {\n  100 |       const targetPage = Math.max(1, Math.min(initialPage, totalPages))\n> 101 |       setCurrentPage(targetPage)\n      |       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  102 |     }\n  103 |   }, [totalPages, initialPage, currentPage])\n  104 |","Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/Users/macbook/github code/Nabu/src/renderer/src/features/pdf/PdfViewer.tsx:176:5\n  174 |   // Changing zoom invalidates cached rasterisations — re-render at new scale\n  175 |   useEffect(() => {\n> 176 |     setPageImages({})\n      |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  177 |   }, [scale])\n  178 |\n  179 |   // Create an annotation from the current text selection on a page image","Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/Users/macbook/github code/Nabu/src/renderer/src/features/search/CommandPalette.tsx:91:5\n  89 |   // Reset selection when debounced query changes.\n  90 |   useEffect(() => {\n> 91 |     setSelectedIndex(0)\n     |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  92 |   }, [debouncedQuery])\n  93 |\n  94 |   // Auto-focus the input on mount.","Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/Users/macbook/github code/Nabu/src/renderer/src/features/search/QuickSwitcher.tsx:91:5\n  89 |   // Reset selection when query or debounced query changes.\n  90 |   useEffect(() => {\n> 91 |     setSelectedIndex(0)\n     |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  92 |   }, [debouncedQuery])\n  93 |\n  94 |   // Auto-focus the input on mount.","Error: Cannot access variable before it is declared\n\n`performSearch` is accessed before it is declared, which prevents the earlier access from updating when this value changes over time.\n\n/Users/macbook/github code/Nabu/src/renderer/src/features/search/SearchPanel.tsx:108:7\n  106 |   useEffect(() => {\n  107 |     if (query.trim()) {\n> 108 |       performSearch(query)\n      |       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ `performSearch` accessed before it is declared\n  109 |     }\n  110 |     // Only run on mount — query changes via input are handled by the debounce\n  111 |     // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n\n/Users/macbook/github code/Nabu/src/renderer/src/features/search/SearchPanel.tsx:120:3\n  118 |\n  119 |   // --- Debounced search ---\n> 120 |   const performSearch = useCallback(\n      |   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 121 |     async (q: string) => {\n      | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 122 |       if (!q.trim()) {\n      …\n      | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 139 |     [onResultsChange]\n      | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 140 |   )\n      | ^^^^ `performSearch` is declared here\n  141 |\n  142 |   const handleInputChange = useCallback(\n  143 |     (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {","react-hooks/preserve-manual-memoization","Compilation Skipped: Existing memoization could not be preserved\n\nReact Compiler has skipped optimizing this component because the existing manual memoization could not be preserved. This value was memoized in source but not in compilation output.\n\n/Users/macbook/github code/Nabu/src/renderer/src/features/search/SearchPanel.tsx:121:5\n  119 |   // --- Debounced search ---\n  120 |   const performSearch = useCallback(\n> 121 |     async (q: string) => {\n      |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 122 |       if (!q.trim()) {\n      | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 123 |         onResultsChange([])\n      …\n      | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 137 |       }\n      | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 138 |     },\n      | ^^^^^^ Could not preserve existing memoization\n  139 |     [onResultsChange]\n  140 |   )\n  141 |","React Hook useEffect has missing dependencies: 'performSearch' and 'query'. Either include them or remove the dependency array.",["2703"],["2704"],"'_setDictationAvailable' is assigned a value but never used.","react-hooks/rules-of-hooks","React Hook \"useState\" is called conditionally. React Hooks must be called in the exact same order in every component render.","React Hook \"useEffect\" is called conditionally. React Hooks must be called in the exact same order in every component render.","Replace `⏎········.set('clipboardShortcut',·combo)⏎········` with `.set('clipboardShortcut',·combo)`",{"range":"2705","text":"2706"},"Insert `⏎······················`",{"range":"2707","text":"2708"},{"range":"2709","text":"2552"},{"range":"2710","text":"2552"},"Replace `contextMenuTarget.path,·renameValue,·state.currentFile,·dispatch` with `⏎······contextMenuTarget.path,⏎······renameValue,⏎······state.currentFile,⏎······dispatch⏎····`",{"range":"2711","text":"2712"},"React Hook \"useMemo\" is called conditionally. React Hooks must be called in the exact same order in every component render. Did you accidentally call a React Hook after an early return?","React Hook \"useCallback\" is called conditionally. React Hooks must be called in the exact same order in every component render. Did you accidentally call a React Hook after an early return?",{"range":"2713","text":"2317"},{"range":"2714","text":"2317"},{"range":"2715","text":"2317"},"Delete `,`",{"range":"2716","text":"2317"},"Replace `filePath:·string` with `⏎··filePath:·string⏎`",{"range":"2717","text":"2718"},"Reaching to \"./assets/main.css\" is not allowed.","Reaching to \"katex/dist/katex.min.css\" is not allowed.","Reaching to \"react-dom/client\" is not allowed.","Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/Users/macbook/github code/Nabu/src/renderer/src/shared/components/OutlinePanel.tsx:80:5\n  78 |   // IntersectionObserver — track the heading currently in view (Req 7.4).\n  79 |   useEffect(() => {\n> 80 |     setActiveIndex(null)\n     |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  81 |\n  82 |     const elements: Element[] = []\n  83 |     for (const entry of entries) {","Replace `.query(query)` with `⏎··········.query(query)⏎··········`",{"range":"2719","text":"2720"},{"range":"2721","text":"2552"},"Replace `})` with `··})⏎··········`",{"range":"2722","text":"2723"},["2724","2725"],["2726"],{"range":"2727","text":"2317"},"Replace `|·'blue'⏎··|·'red'⏎··|·'green'⏎··|·'yellow'⏎··|·'purple'⏎··|·'orange'⏎··|·'cyan'⏎·` with `'blue'·|·'red'·|·'green'·|·'yellow'·|·'purple'·|·'orange'·|·'cyan'`",{"range":"2728","text":"2729"},"Replace `·?·(updatedActive?.path·??·state.currentFile)` with `⏎············?·(updatedActive?.path·??·state.currentFile)⏎···········`",{"range":"2730","text":"2731"},"Replace `·...syncActiveAliases({·...state,·openTabs·}),·editMode:·true,·currentRaw:·action.payload` with `⏎········...syncActiveAliases({·...state,·openTabs·}),⏎········editMode:·true,⏎········currentRaw:·action.payload⏎·····`",{"range":"2732","text":"2733"},"no-useless-escape","Unnecessary escape character: \\-.","unnecessaryEscape",["2734","2735"],{"range":"2736","text":"2343"},{"range":"2737","text":"2317"},"Replace `⏎··index:·Map<string,·Set<string>>,⏎··filePath:·string⏎` with `index:·Map<string,·Set<string>>,·filePath:·string`",{"range":"2738","text":"2739"},["2740","2741"],["2742"],["2743","2744"],["2745"],["2746","2747"],["2748"],["2749","2750"],["2751"],["2752","2753"],["2754"],"'_getAST' is defined but never used.","'execSync' is defined but never used.",["2755"],"'electron' is defined but never used.",["2756"],"'emptyState' is assigned a value but never used.","'mainEntry' is assigned a value but never used.","'AppAction' is defined but never used.",["2757"],"'stateManager' is assigned a value but never used.",["2758","2759"],"'_filePath' is defined but never used.","'_isExternal' is defined but never used.",["2760","2761"],["27